Source:  Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page:  14
Edition:
Quote:  ... the central Bay of Plenty `mystery ship' ... could very well be a very large `Kon-Tiki' fishing device. ... [Footnote:] A `kon-tiki' is a small raft used by fishermen to drift their lines out well beyond the breakers using wind assistance. They are controlled by a line from the shore.
